<h2> Table of Contents (<a href="http://www.cs.uic.edu/~liub/book/Table-of-Contents-2nd-edition.pdf">Full Version</a>, Second Edition)</h2>
<ol>
<li> Introduction
<li> Association Rules and Sequential Patterns
<li> Supervised Learning
<li> Unsupervised Learning
<li> Partially Supervised Learning
<li> Information Retrieval and Web Search
<li> Social Network Analysis
<li> Web Crawling
<li> Structured Data Extraction: Wrapper Generation
<li> Information Integration
<li> Opinion Mining and Sentiment Anlaysis
<Li> Web Usage Mining
</ol>
<p> Chapters 8 was written by <a href ="http://www.informatics.indiana.edu/fil/">Prof. Filippo Menczer</a>. Chapter 12 was mainly written by <a href="http://maya.cs.depaul.edu/~mobasher/">Prof. Bamshad Mobasher </a> and <a href="http://louisville.edu/speed/computer/people/faculty/nasraoui">Prof. Olfa Nasraoui</a> (second edition) except the recommender systems section for which they also helped. <a href="http://www.comp.nus.edu.sg/~leews/">Prof. Wee Sun Lee</a> helped a great deal in the writing of Chapter 5. They are all international experts in their fields. 

